The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, May 20: The Centre said today it had no information on the arrest of Ulfa commander-in-chief Paresh Barua. There is no information regarding Baruas arrest, home secretary G.K. Pillai told a news channel.          
	Military intelligence sources, however, said a suspect said to be Barua was picked up in Dhaka and could be kept in a Bangladesh jail after being booked in a Chittagong arms case. The sources also said a person said to be Anup Chetia was picked up in Mymensingh and sent to Delhi.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Ravi Shankaran, one of the main accused in the naval war room leak case, has been arrested in London. The CBI has sought his early extradition. A kin of former Naval Chief Arun Prakash, Shankaran, 40, was arrested by London police on April 21.                  
	Kalimpong: Three persons on a search-and-rescue mission drowned in the Teesta this morning when their raft was sucked into a whirlpool in the mountain river. One person was still missing but seven others in the raft swam to safety.                   
	Chandigarh (PTI): A court has deferred the verdict on the plea for enhancing the sentence of former Haryana police chief S.P.S. Rathore in the Ruchika Girhotra molestation case to May 25. The court said it would take five more days to write the judgment.
                                                                                                                                              
